  "name": "Morrison COU2 — VAD hemolysis credibility assessment (W-ON-02 adversarial)",
  "description": "V&V 40 credibility assessment for CFD hemolysis prediction of the FDA generic centrifugal blood pump under ventricular assist device (VAD) conditions. COU2 evaluates whether the computational model can predict absolute hemolysis levels for a Class III VAD device at Model Risk Level 5. Higher model risk drives stricter credibility requirements; Monte Carlo uncertainty quantification is performed. All 13 credibility factors are assessed; achieved levels meet or exceed required levels at MRL 5. Decision: Accepted. Note: the ContextOfUse describes operating ranges in prose but carries no structured hasApplicabilityConstraint or hasOperatingEnvelope link, leaving the model's bounded domain of validity formally unspecified (W-ON-02).",
