      "factorStatus": "assessed",
      "acceptanceCriteria": "Hemolysis index is directly mapped to clinical endpoint; QoI traceability documented.",
      "rationale": "Normalized index of hemolysis (NIH) is the primary regulatory QoI. Mapping from CFD scalar stress exposure to NIH is documented with literature-supported power-law model. QoI is directly used in 510(k) submission."
