      "acceptanceCriteria": "Governing equations appropriate for viscous incompressible rotating flow; hemolysis power-law model justified by literature and sensitivity analysis.",
      "rationale": "Reynolds-Averaged Navier-Stokes with SST k-omega turbulence closure selected based on rotating machinery benchmark studies. Giersiepen power-law hemolysis model with Heuser-Opitz constants validated against published datasets. Model form uncertainty estimated at ±22%."
    },
    {
      "type": "CredibilityFactor",
      "factorType": "Model inputs",
      "factorStandard": "ASME-VV40-2018",
      "requiredLevel": 4,
      "achievedLevel": 4,
      "factorStatus": "assessed",
      "acceptanceCriteria": "All material properties and boundary conditions characterised with quantified uncertainty; Monte Carlo propagation performed.",
      "rationale": "Blood viscosity, density, and hemolysis model exponents treated as uncertain inputs. Distributions assigned from literature meta-analysis. Monte Carlo with 2000 samples propagates input uncertainty to NIH predictions. 95th-percentile NIH remains below clinical threshold."
